[recto] Ad [Addendum] 54. Witt Library. Under P.B.I. Kermesse with stage in center, next to it on the right with people on thatched roof, with 'Reiger' on left: A) with three men (or boys?) wrestling on ground in bottom left corner; 1) Cambridge, Fitzwilliam, 'P.B.I. Village Fest, Photo; 2) Clarembaux, Canvas 180 x 120 cm (old photo); 3) Private Coll. Genoa; 4) Perth Property of the town, presented (as stated in a newspaper cutting of 27-2-1937) many years ago by Mr Seaton Watson of Aytoun House; [verso] Glenfarg, 5ft. 10,1 in. x 5 ft. 3in. (S. Watson spent a large amount of time abroad and especially in Austria. Made into an upright by addidition of sky [onleesbaar]; B) Without the wrestlers: 1) Grazer Galerie, signed 'P;4 114 x 168 cm; 2) Sale Fiévez, Brussels 17-18-V-1923, N° 15, B. 114 x 165 (damaged).
